I have purchased many Archos products since their first mp3 player, and have always been pleased with them. This, however, has been a huge disappointment, and I will be returning it shortly.The first problem I encountered was the plastic protector on the screen. When I removed it, it left glue all over the screen, and I have not been able to completely remove it, leaving the surface sticky.The sensors aren't very good, in order to select an item, I usually have to tap on it multiple times, using a lot of pressure. And despite having calibrated it several times, it often selects something other than what I am trying to open. It happens sometimes when I am trying to select an icon, but happens every time I am trying to enter text. I use touch screens on several other devices and have never had this problem before (in other words, I do not believe this is user error).When I attempt to connect to the internet (the whole reason I purchased this item), I get some message about how I can't connect to some google-related ad page. There is no place to enter a web address, and as far as I can see, no way to set a default page. Perhaps those things exist, but in light of the other issues I'm having with this device, I'm not even inclined to investigate further.This could be a great little device, unfortunately, Archos missed the mark as far as I'm concerned.
