Long story short:This tablet is a case study in "you get what you pay for".  Yes, it's 40% the cost of an iPad, but it's 100% useless.  The software that comes on this device is terrible, and this device is not compatible with the Android Marketplace.  There's literally nothing you can do with it.Full Review:The build quality is solid, but that's about all I can say in its favor.  The Industrial Design is ugly, as is the the screen.  It runs an older version of the Android OS (1.5) as having an older touch screen technology which you will hate.  My thinking was, I would be willing to put up with this for a cheap platform on which to run Android apps but the deal breaker is this-- *NO* access to the Android Marketplace.They do provide their own app store but it is awful.  Many apps appear to be in foreign (Asian) languages.  To add insult to injury, the applications that come with the device are horrible and without access to the marketplace-- you can't find alternatives.I thought... It sucks as a ebook reader, music player, video player, internet browser, and can't download applications... Maybe it would make a good living room clock!  Alas, the only clock application is ugly as anything.  I do not know what the reason for not including the marketplace on the device was but it damns the Archos 7 to uselessness.
